  "commentary": "With SPX at 6816.3 sitting between the flip at 6796 and the massive +83.3B gamma wall at 6830, dealers are likely covering short hedges into this 3.4% decline and will aggressively sell any bounce toward 6830. The PIN regime with heavy positive gamma concentration from 6810-6840 creates a strong magnet effect that should contain upside momentum and encourage mean reversion back toward the 6820-6830 zone. Watch 6796 as the critical level - a break below flips dealers to negative gamma and removes the stabilizing bid.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get pulled back up toward 6830 but with a hard ceiling there.",
